HEADWORD: mistiming
<hw>mistiming</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of assigning
something to a time when it could not have existed or
occurred.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> anachronism, misdating.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mistiness</ent>⟦br⟧
